This memorandum, addressed to the Secretary of State, delegates authority to the Secretary to provide assistance to Ukraine under sections 506(a)(1) and 552(c)(2) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. Specifically, the Secretary is authorized to direct the drawdown of up to $450 million in defense articles and services, as well as military education and training, from the Department of Defense. Additionally, the Secretary is authorized to direct the drawdown of up to $10 million in commodities and services from any agency of the United States Government. The Secretary is also responsible for making the necessary determinations required under these sections to direct such drawdowns. The memorandum concludes by directing the publication of this memorandum in the Federal Register.